      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I agree that the added layer of human review will inevitably slow down the process, but I believe the increased attention to detail will lead to more accurate and robust analyses, which in the long run, can offset potential speed gains. In addition, allowing human review paralegals and support staff to familiarize themselves with important case dynamics may help teams develop a more nuanced understanding of complex issues. While the immediate impact may be noticeable, the quality of research outcomes could improve significantly in the near term.",
